	<entry>
		<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: help with Translation/Prononciation-- "saMskRti"]]></title>
		<link rel="alternate" href="http://spokensanskrit.de/board/forum/viewtopic.php?pid=2529#p2529"/>
		<content type="html"><![CDATA[<div class="quotebox"><cite>melissab wrote:</cite><blockquote><div><p>Hello talented Sanskrit translators. </p><p>On the site, &quot;saMskRti&quot; is listed as meaning culture and also civilization. Could anyone please verify this, and help clarify the translation, ie; in what context the word might be used?</p><p>Most importantly, could someone please give me the exact oral pronunciation of the word? Where is the emphasis placed? My instinct is to pronounce it as &quot;sam-SKREE-tee&quot; but I doubt this is correct. could anyone please help?</p></div></blockquote></div><p>Even though you are not addressing me, I will make an uneducated comment.</p><p>Yes, the meanings are correct.</p><p>People will pronounce it differently in different parts of India. What you want to pronounce is also fine. Sanskrit was spoken over thousands of kilometres width over thousands of years, and I doubt if there was ever a single correct pronunciation valid all over that area.</p>]]></content>
		<author>
			<name><![CDATA[1wrongaddress]]></name>
