	<entry>
		<title type="html"><![CDATA[help with Translation/Prononciation-- "saMskRti"]]></title>
		<link rel="alternate" href="http://spokensanskrit.de/board/forum/viewtopic.php?pid=2520#p2520"/>
		<content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Hello talented Sanskrit translators. </p><p>On the site, &quot;saMskRti&quot; is listed as meaning culture and also civilization. Could anyone please verify this, and help clarify the translation, ie; in what context the word might be used?</p><p>Most importantly, could someone please give me the exact oral pronunciation of the word? Where is the emphasis placed? My instinct is to pronounce it as &quot;sam-SKREE-tee&quot; but I doubt this is correct. could anyone please help?</p>]]></content>
